data.description: Beautiful and updated home by McAllister Park with large yard and in a cul-de-sac! Owners have done the heavy lifting by installing new HVAC in 2021, replacing all windows and fence in 2022, and in 2023 they completed backyard landscaping, installed top of the line water softener, remodeled the pantry/laundry room, and installed new blinds.  Seller's VA loan rate of 3.25% may be assumed by qualified buyers. Home features open kitchen with white cabinets, granite countertops and a breakfast bar. Wood burning fireplace and separate dining room.  Upstairs you will find the game room and the 3 bedrooms.  The large primary bedroom has a sizable walk-in closest, sitting area space, and an en-suite bathroom with separate jetted garden tub/shower and double sinks.  Almost a quarter of an acre, the backyard has a patio, large shed in cement pad, and a playground - making it perfect to entertain. Owners stayed nice and warm during the 2021 snow storm without loss of utilities.  Easy access to 281/410. McAllister Park nearby. Plenty of dining choices and shopping nearby. Short commute to Joint Base San Antonio, Stone Oak and much, much more - making this property a great home or an excellent rental property. Welcome home!
